<b>effects - </b>1/4/02 12:08:35 PM<br>~ <b>Kocho Divah</b><blockquote>To the below question, your level relative to the mob, your charisma, your wind skill, will all determine whether a charm will stick or be resisted. As for an exact formula, we do not have. Its been debated how much charisma a bard really needs.<br><br>I myself use Charm (the higher level charm) alot at level 56. By this time, a few mobs are too high too charm (51+), but I find that out after trying it anyway. If they're charmable, I still get a few resists now and then. I have 180 charisma, Wind skill of 207 (yeah, need to max it out), and am always going to be more than a few levels above the mob.</blockquote></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#eeeeee"><td>
